created attachment 9366445
extension.zip

steps to reproduce:

- install the attached extension on firefox for android
- open the popup
- click the link that says "click here to download"


actual results:

on desktop firefox (v120), a download is started for a file hello-world.txt upon clicking the link.

on android (v122), nothing happens. i can verify with a debugger that the same code is invoked, but nothing happens.


expected results:

android and desktop should behave consistently - e.g. android should also initiate a download. the extension attaches an onclick handler to a link which creates a new <a> element, sets the href and download attributes, and calls click() to emulate a click on that element:

document.getelementbyid("download").onclick = function() {
    const link = document.createelement("a");
    link.href = "data:,";
    for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
        link.href += "helloworld";
    }
    link.download = "hello-world.txt";
    link.click();
    return false;
}

this is unfortunately blocking enabling my firefox extension for android, since i rely on this mechanism to trigger downloads. there may be other ways to trigger the download (browser.downloads?), but i've been a fan of this method for not requiring additional permissions and for being relatively simple. i'm not sure why there'd be a difference between desktop and android in any event.
